heres the process for how we set weights just for clarity:

1. get latest predictions from each miner ready to be reviewed
2. get weighted RMSE of the latest set of predictions from each miner
3. convert RMSE to an inverted normal distribution (higher scores are better)
4. add the normal distribution to a historical weighted average using information on how difficult the move was to predict
5. perform an aggressive yeojohnson distribution on the updated weighted averages
6. normalize the yeojohnson results, set weights using the normalization
when we say "more aggressive" we're talking about step 5 and the aggressiveness of our yeojohnson distribution
